article.description: — Antonio Daye Jr. had 22 points as Fordham routed St. Francis (N.Y.) 68-46 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Daye Jr. leads Fordham past St. Francis (N.Y.) 68-46
article.linkText: Daye Jr. leads Fordham past St. Francis (N.Y.) 68-46
article.story: NEW YORK -- — Antonio Daye Jr. had 22 points as Fordham routed St. Francis (N.Y.) 68-46 on Wednesday night. Chuba Ohams added 20 points, 22 rebounds and three blocks. The career-high in points and rebounds is the first 20-20 game for the Rams since Damon Lopez 1991. Antrell Charlton had eight rebounds for Fordham (6-3). Darius Quisenberry, whose 19.0 points per game entering the contest led the Rams, scored 4 points on 1-of-13 shooting. Larry Moreno had 13 points for the Terriers (0-7). Michael Cubbage added 13 points and nine rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
